The Exalenz clinical investigation is a multicenter, non-randomized, study of the C-Octanoate Breath Test (OBT).

 The present study is a feasibility trial, which aims to evaluate the capability of the OBT measurement to differentiate between presence and absence of HCC determined by Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) in patients with chronic liver disease.

